solution: 
```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int findLUSlength(string a, string b) {
        if (a == b) return -1;
        return max(a.size(), b.size());
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n + m)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution checks if the two strings are equal. If they are, it returns -1 as there's no uncommon subsequence. If not, it returns the maximum length between the two strings, which represents the longest uncommon subsequence.

